The paper proposes a novel approach for relation extraction from free text using embedding models, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research (cs.CL). The approach also involves using existing knowledge from a knowledge base, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and knowledge representation (cs.AI). The use of embeddings for learning low-dimensional representations of words and entities is a common technique in deep learning and neural networks (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the approach on a dataset of New York Times articles, which involves information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) techniques.
